    • Constructor Detail

      • Notebook

        public Notebook​(java.lang.String notebookName)
        A Notebook constructor that allows user to set it's name. With a new notebook, an empty SortedList of taskLists and activeTaskList is constructed. The current task list is set to activeTaskList. The isChanged status is set to true.
        Parameters:
        notebookName - a string that holds the notebook's name

        Parameters:
        file - a string that holds the location to save the notebook

        public void setChanged​(boolean isChanged)

        isChanged - is a boolean

      • addTaskList

        public void addTaskList​(TaskList taskList)
        A method that adds the given task list to taskLists and updates isChanged to true. Also checks that the name of the given taskList is not a duplicate. Once added into taskLists, the list is set as the currentTaskList.
        Parameters:
        taskList - list of type TaskList that will be added to task lists
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - with message "Invalid name." if the given taskList name equals "Active Tasks"
